<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Ready to Host OIC Contact Group on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Joschka
Fischer on Saturday announced Bonn's readiness to host a meeting
of foreign ministers from Islamic countries to discuss the Kosovo
crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone conversation with his Iranian counterpart Kamal
Kharrazi, Fischer said that Germany welcomes the visit to Bonn by
the foreign ministers of the Organization of the Islamic
conference (OIC) contact group on Kosovo, the Islamic Republic
News Agency (IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
"As the current chairman of the European Union (EU), Germany
welcomes efforts by the Islamic nations to resolve the crisis in
Kosovo," he said, adding that Bonn is keen on exchanging views
with OIC contact group.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the OIC contact group on Wednesday met
in Geneva on the Kosovo crisis, underling that the ethnic
Albanians in Kosovo should be allowed to determine their own
political future.
</P>
<P>
The OIC contact group, which include Iran, Malaysia, Pakistan,
Turkey, Morocco, Senegal, Egypt and Saudi Arabia, also announced
readiness to contact with other countries and international forums
to find a political solution to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
However, no report is available so far about any possible
ministerial meeting of the OIC contact group in Bonn.
</P>
<P>
In the conversation, Kharrazi voiced the concern of Islamic
countries over the ongoing human tragedy facing Kosovo ethnic
Albanians and briefed his German counterpart on the results of
the recent meeting of OIC contact group in Geneva.
</P>
<P>
The world of Islam cannot be indifferent towards the ongoing
massacres of the Muslims in the Balkans, said the Iranian
official, whose country is the current OIC chairman.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi also noted that the OIC is prepared to make serious
efforts to resolve the Kosovo crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
