<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-10 19:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Cultural Week Opens in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Cultural
Week, which is aimed at expanding cultural exchanges between
China and Kuwait, was inaugurated here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the Week, the first of its kind
since the 1991 Gulf war, singers and dancers from China's
southwest Guizhou Province entertained an audience of some 500
people with brilliant Chinese folk songs and dances.
</P>
<P>
As part of the activities, over 65 traditional Chinese
paintings and watercolor paintings were exhibited at Kuwait's
Abdul-Aziz Hussein Cultural Center.
</P>
<P>
During the cultural week, China and Kuwait will also sign
a three-year executive plan concerning bilateral cultural
exchanges within the framework of a cultural agreement reached
between the two countries in 1982.
</P>
<P>
According to the draft plan, both sides will make great efforts
to encourage and facilitate exchanges in the fields of arts and
culture, media, education, sports, and social welfare and
development.
</P>
<P>
According to officials from the Chinese Embassy in Kuwait,
Kuwait's television station will broadcast documentaries about the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait held a cultural week in China in 1997, which included
art exhibition, lectures and folk songs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
