<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Army Head: Ground Troops in Kosovo Not Necessary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN April 27 (Xinhua)--The NATO air strikes against Yugoslavia
have achieved such a progress that deployment of ground combat
troops in Kosovo is no longer an essential task, General Inspector
of German forces Hans-Peter von Kirchbach said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"If we strike the balance now, we will see that we achieve the
progress," von Kirchbach told the Focus news weekly, adding,"there
is no need to deploy ground troops."
</P>
<P>
The four-star-general leading the German forces stressed there
was no reason for the escalation of the NATO air campaign, and the
NATO would continue the operations until reaching its goal.
</P>
<P>
"We must carry out with determination what we have planned,"
von Kirchbach said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
