<DOCNO> XIE19990411.0004 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Leone Rebel Leaders to Meet in Togo on April 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone rebel leader Foday
Sankoh, who is being detained in capital Freetown, will meet his
battlefield commanders in Togo on April 18, Togolese government
officials said in Lome Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here, the officials disclosed
that the meeting will take place in Kara, the hometown of Togolese
President Gnassinghe Eyadema who is to host the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leonean President Ahmad Tejan Kabbah announced earlier
this year that he agreed to let Sankoh to meet his commanders.
</P>
<P>
The Togolese officials noted that Sam Bockarie, chief
battlefield commander of the rebel Revolutionary United Front,
will be in the Togolese northern town for the talks.
</P>
<P>
Togolese President Eyadema, also the chairman of the Economic
Community of West African States (ECOWAS), agreed to host the
talks between the rebel leaders in Togo in preparation for peace
talks between the Sierra Leonean government and the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh was sentenced to death for treason last October and is
appealing against the conviction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
