<HEADLINE> Bonn Demands Belgrade Aid for Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN April 10 (Xinhua)--German Foreign Minister Joschka Fischer
issued Saturday a demand for Yugoslavia to provide urgent
humanitarian relief to Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade must set up its own relief network to alleviate the
suffering of an estimated 300,000 starving refugees, Fischer said.
</P>
<P>
Fischer said he has evidence that some 100,000 ethnic Albanian
refugees were "brought by force from the Macedonian border back
into Kosovo".
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, German Interior Minister Otto Schily said that his
ministry has earmarked some 10 million marks for the refugee
relief effort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
