<HEADLINE> Anti-war Protest Staged Outside U.S. Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN April 10 (Xinhua)--A sit-in protest against the NATO air
strikes over Yugoslavia was staged Saturday outside the main gate
of the U.S. Spangdahlem military base in west Germany.
</P>
<P>
About 50 demonstrators carrying banners demanding an immediate
end to the air raids blocked the road until late afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Spangdahlem, in the state of Rhineland palatinate, is the
biggest U.S. air force base in Europe.
</P>
<P>
About thirteen U.S. F-117 Stealth fighter bombers stationed in
Spangdahlem reportedly took part in the NATO air campaigns since
April.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Stealth bomber unit at the base said the
sit-in was not disrupting regular F-117 operations against
Yugoslavia launched from the base. 
</P>
</TEXT>
