<HEADLINE> Oman, Jordan Willing to Enhance Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Oman and Jordan are willing to
enhance bilateral cooperation in all fields, Oman's official news
agency said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein and Omani Sultan
Qaboos Bin Said expressed the desire in their talks Saturday in
Minh province, about 160 kilometers south of the capital Muscat,
the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders pointed out that closer cooperation will serve
"the interests and goals" of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, the two leaders also discussed the latest
developments of the international and regional situation,
especially the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Oman, where the 37-year-old Jordanian monarch is paying a
one-day visit, is part of his Arab tour to strengthen friendly
relations with the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The tour, which has taken him to Saudi Arabia, also includes
stops in the United Arab Emirates, Syria, Libya, Qatar and Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah took the throne in February after the death of his
father King Hussein. 
</P>
</TEXT>
