<HEADLINE> UAE Receives First Palestinian Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
Saturday received the first Palestinian flight, which landed at
the Abu Dhabi International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Aboard the plane, which took off from Gaza Airport, were
Chairman of the Palestinian Civil Aviation Authority Fa'ez Arif
Zaidan, senior officials of the Palestinian Airline and the Gaza
International Airport, and a number of Palestinian businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamdan bin Mubarak Al Nahyan, chairman of the Abu Dhabi
Civil Aviation Department, received the Palestinian delegation
and praised them for their efforts in operating flights to various
Arab capitals from Gaza Airport, the official news agency WAM said.
</P>
<P>
Emphasizing the importance of the first Palestinian flight to
Abu Dhabi, Fa'ez said it was the first step towards opening
similar flights to other Gulf countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the Palestinian Airline was planning to open ways of
cooperation with a number of Arab cities.
</P>
<P>
Hamdan assured the Palestinian delegation that the UAE would
give the necessary support to the Palestinian Airline in order to
maintain the link between the two brotherly countries in the
field of aviation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
