<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in Denver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DENVER, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji arrived
here Saturday to continue his eight-day official visit to the
United States after spending two busy days in Washington.
</P>
<P>
At the airport, the Chinese premier was greeted by Colorado
Governor Bill Owens, Denver Mayor Wellington Webb and hundreds of
people from the Chinese community.
</P>
<P>
In Denver, the third stop of his visit, Zhu will meet local
officials and tour enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Denver, nicknamed as "Mile High City," lies 25 kilometers east
of the Rocky Mountains and enjoys a spectacular view of some of
the highest peaks in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The city has been rated the fourth best city in the United
States for starting a new business and was singled out for having
the fastest growing economy in the country for the past three
years, according to latest edition of Travel-host Magazine.
</P>
</TEXT>
