<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Fight Against Illegal Employment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 10 (xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Labor and Social Affairs said here Saturday that measures would be
taken against individuals and private entities that are illegally
sending Ethiopians abroad for employment.
</P>
<P>
"No agency has so far been licensed to engage in such business
and most of the people sent by these illegal agencies are being
victims of violent attacks," sources with the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The official Ethiopian News Agency quoted the sources as saying
that several "unqualified" individuals who applied to engage in
employment services since the issuance of the "private employment
agency proclamation" a year ago have been turned down.
</P>
<P>
Information reaching the ministry indicate that the Ethiopians,
 especially young women, who have been sent abroad by the "illegal
 employment agencies", are being abused while some were killed in
violence.
</P>
<P>
However, the sources said that with the support of the police,
the ministry is taking legal measures against the culprits.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
