<DOCNO> XIE19990411.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO Says Weather Against Operation Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A NATO spokesman said here
Saturday that poor weather had some impact on NATO air strikes in
Yugoslavia over last 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
NATO military spokesman K. Freytag told a news briefing that
the weather "hindered us significantly and affected our
operation". One group of combat aircraft flew and further three
were canceled due to the weather, he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also confirmed that a radio relay facility near
Pristina was destroyed among the strategic targets hit by NATO
during Friday night and early Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Through a video, the reporters at NATO headquarters watched the
pictures about the pre-and-post strike over the radio relay
station.
</P>
<P>
When asked about military purpose of the bombing against the
radio relay tower in Pristina, Freytag said the relay station has
been used for military end and has become the legitimate military
target. "That's why we took it out."
</P>
<P>
Asked if a mistaken bombing near a main phone exchange center
in Pristina happened because of mistaken information, NATO
political spokesman Jamie Shea said the accurate information
always delayed, and he hopes to get updated information as early
as possible. "It's best for you, and best for me."
</P>
<P>
"One of the bombs targeted on the facility may have span off
and been responsible for damage of surrounding building. However,
I believe that it was clear from the slide shown here, that
everybody could see graphically what it was struck, that the
collateral damage was very, very limited indeed, it was not on a
massive city busting scale, and it was very, very localized
indeed, " Shea said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also talked another reason why the collateral
damage is minor. "Given the fact that so many people have been
forced out Pristina, and I don't think it's any doubt about that,
there are well-documented television picture that showed the city
is close to a ghost town that I have seen recently."
</P>
<P>
"Clearly the damage to the civilians would have also been, I
think a harm to civilians, moderate even if, of course, I don't
have an exact figure to give you," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
