<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Expansion of Tehran-Pretoria Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis (parliament)
Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nour here on Saturday called for
expansion of political and economic ties between Iran and South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with the visiting South African Foreign Minister
Alfred Nzo, Nouri said given the great potentials and capabilities
existing in the two countries, the present level of economic
exchanges between Tehran and Pretoria is inadequate.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that obstacles standing in the way of implementing
the agreements signed between the two countries would be
identified and removed through the concerted efforts of relevant
officials, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Underling the need to harmonize bilateral political and
economic ties, the Iranian speaker said that promoting the level
of parliamentary ties would pave the way for the expansion of
all-out ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He also praised the independent policies pursued by South
African President Nelson Mandela on international issues.
</P>
<P>
Nzo, who arrived here on Thursday to attend the fourth joint
Tehran-Pretoria economic commission, also hoped that the obstacles
standing in the way of implementing the agreements between the two
countries would be removed.
</P>
<P>
He described the close parliamentary ties between the two
countries as "very important" and voiced his country's readiness
to further expand these ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
