<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 13 Others Wounded in Fires in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and 13
others wounded on Saturday in a fire and an explosion in Egypt's
two biggest cities.
</P>
<P>
Two fire fighters died and 10 people were wounded when a burning
warehouse collapsed in the Cairo suburb of Giza, the country's
Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The walls of the warehouse, which housed sets for several
television soap operas, fell on top of the two fire fighters,
including a lieutenant colonel, the agency quoted police sources
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Several other fire fighters sustained serious burns, but are in
stable condition in hospital, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The fire destroyed an estimated 7 million Egyptian pounds
(about 2.1 million U.S. dollars) worth of television decor. Among
the sets destroyed include those of a soap opera about late
Egyptian singer Om Kalthum.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an electricity transformer exploded in the
Mediterranean port city of Alexandria, 210 kilometers northwest of
the capital, killing a technician and wounding three others.
</P>
<P>
The explosion and consequent fire caused a power outage in the
Moharam Beih area. Fire fighters took two hours to extinguish the
blaze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
