<HEADLINE> New Clews Found to Assassination of Iranian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The senior Iranian military
commander Brigadier General Ali Sayyad Shirazi was gunned down
Saturday morning by an assassin disguised as Tehran city street
cleaner, the evening daily Kayhan reported.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said that the assassin fired three shots in his
head when Shirazi was driving out of his house to send his child
to school on his way to work.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Iranian armed forces, quoted by the
Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA), said earlier that Shirazi,
deputy chief of the joint staff of Iranian armed forces, was
killed at 0645 hours local times (0215 GMT) as he left home for
work.
</P>
<P>
The statement did not give more details about the assassination
and the identities of the assassin. However, IRNA reported that
the Iranian outlawed Mujahideen Khalq Organization (MKO) has
claimed responsibility for the killing.
</P>
<P>
The Iraq-based MKO said that Shirazi was targeted because he
was responsible for purging and executing military personnel, and
responsible for the death of hundreds of thousands of teenagers in
the war with Iraq (1980-88), reports said.
</P>
<P>
Shirazi, born in 1944, served as commander of the Iranian
army's ground forces during the Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
The MKO, the main armed Iranian opposition group, has claimed
responsibility for several assassinations in Iran, including
the killing of Assadollah Lajevardi, the former head of Iran's
Prisons Organization in last August.
</P>
<P>
The MKO was a main political group which had fought against the
former Iranian shah regime, but it was outlawed in 1981 due to
sharp difference with the Iranian government.
</P>
<P>
During the past decades, the MKO launched various attacks on
Iranian interests inside and outside Iran. In retaliation, the
Iranian armed forces also bombed the MKO bases in Iraq several
times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
