The Bangladeshi government has declared a general holiday on
Monday in the seven cities to enable people to cast their votes,
while the Home Ministry has imposed a ban on carrying fire arms in
the election areas.
</P>
<P>
It is not immediately known whether the opposition parties will
participate in the elections.
</P>
<P>
Elections to 136 of the country's 182 municipalities were held
in February this year amid strong resistance from the opposition
alliance. 
