<HEADLINE> 3 Security Soldiers Wounded in Attack in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Three Turkish security soldiers
were wounded on Sunday in an armed attack by terrorists in
northern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said a group of the terrorists had launched the
armed attack against the security forces in Erbaa town of Tokat
province.
</P>
<P>
The wounded were taken to Tokat State Hospital for medical
treatment, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
A series of bombing attacks have been launched by Kurdish
rebels in protest of the capture of Abdullah Ocalan, who has
led the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) for fighting for
an independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey since August
1984.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan has been jailed on Imrali Island in Marmara Sea near
Turkey's western province of Bursa on charges of treason. He may
face the death penalty if convicted. 
</P>
