<HEADLINE> Qingdao Beats Liaoning in Chinese Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao Hainiu defeated talent-
teemed Liaoning 2-1 in a home match on Sunday, pulling the biggest
upset in the fifth round of China's first division soccer league.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao, who came into the game as the penultimate team on the
league standings, met strong offense in the first 30 minutes but
the hosts' goalkeeper Jiang Hong performed superbly.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made spectacular saves to parry off blasts from
Liaoning's Zhang Yuning, Qu Shengqing and Li Tie.
</P>
<P>
After the goalless first half, Zhou Xin received a pass in the
penalty area in the 54th minute to open the scoring for Qingdao,
who had only two draws and two losses before the game.
</P>
<P>
A Ivanoff header off a corner gave Qingdao a 2-0 lead in the
injury time but in the dying moments Liaoning was consoled when Qu
slotted the ball past Jiang into the net.
</P>
<P>
In Shenyang, defending champion Dalian Wanda had to come back
from behind twice to tie Shenyang Haishi 2-2 away.
</P>
<P>
The tie was the last straw for Dalian coach Xu Genbao, who
announced his resignation at the post-game press conference.
</P>
<P>
"I want to resign because I can no longer brook it any more,"
Xu said. "The club may perform better if I resign now," said Xu,
whose team only managed four draws and one loss in five rounds
this season.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang netted in the 23rd minute to lead 1-0 but Dalian
levelled the score two minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, Dalian beefed up their attacks but Shenyang
surged ahead again with a goal in the 76th minute and Dalian had
waited until two minutes from whistle to equalize.
</P>
<P>
In Tianjin, Chongqing Longxin pulled its first victory this
season by routing hosts Tianjin Taida 2-0. Both goals were scored
in the second half, in the 58th and 85th minute respectively.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Beijing Guo'an succumbed to Guangzhou Songri
1-0 away, Shanghai Shenhua tied with Sichuan Quanxin 1-1 home,
Shandong Taishan upset Jilin Aodong 2-0, while Wuhan beat
Shenzhen 1-0 at home. 
</P>
