<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese City's Airport Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The capital of China's Liaoning
Province has begun a terminal building expansion project at its
Taoxian international airport.
</P>
<P>
The 50,000-sq.m. expansion project will cost one billion yuan.
It accounts for half the entire airport expansion program, which
started at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
When the new airport opens in October of next year, the
terminal will be able to accommodate 6.06 million passengers,
three times the present load.
</P>
<P>
The expansion program also includes improvements to the
communications system, runways, parking lot facilities, and fuel
storage areas.
</P>
<P>
Taoxian airport was built in 1989 and has become an air traffic
hub for northeastern China. Last year, it handled 2.2 million
passengers. 
