<HEADLINE> Bus Bomb Blast Kills Two in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and 25
injured when a bomb explosion ripped through a bus in Central
province of Sri Lanka Sunday, state-run radio said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The bomb went off in a bus that was due to leave Kandy city for
the eastern town of Polonnaruwa in the province. Eight of the
injured were in a serious condition, police in Kandy were quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Police said the bomb was planted by rebels of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) who have been fighting against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the country.
</P>
<P>
No body has claimed responsibility for the bomb blast yet.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Kandy, 112 kilometers from Colombo, was tense
following the explosion, informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
Police are taking action to keep the situation under control,
said the sources, adding that there was a lot of panic as hundreds
of people were coming into Kandy for Sunday shopping when the bomb
went off.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels launched a massive truck bomb attack against
the Buddhist temple in Kandy city in January last year, killing
at least 13 people and injuring many others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
