<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Expansion of Tehran-Bonn Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis (parliament)
Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri here on Sunday called for further
expansion of relations between Iran and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Iran is willing to expand its relations with Germany on the
basis of mutual respect and preservation of national rights, Nouri
told visiting German special envoy and Head of the Federal
Chancellery Bodo Hombach.
</P>
<P>
He said Germany is a country which has great influence in
Europe and a country which enjoys a special status, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Tehran-Bonn relations have undergone ups and downs in recent
years due to the interference of hidden hands who do not favor
promotion of political relations between the two countries, he
said, without elaborating.
</P>
<P>
Terming Hombach's visit to Tehran as "constructive," the
Iranian speaker said that this visit and exchange of visits by
officials of the two countries can prepare a suitable ground for
further promotion of Tehran-Bonn relations.
</P>
<P>
He also underlined the importance of relations between
parliaments of Iran and Germany and called for exchange of
parliamentary delegations and formation of a parliamentary
friendship group between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hombach said in reply that his visit to Iran was aimed at
announcing his country's willingness to expand all-out relations
with Iran.
</P>
<P>
The German official, who arrived here Saturday to submit a
visit invitation of German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder to Iranian
President Mohammad Khatami, also expressed hope that parliamentary
delegations would be exchanged between the two countries in order
to get familiar with each other's outlooks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
