<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Parliament to Set Up China Friendship Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's parliament will set up
a Bangladesh-China Friendship Group to further enhance its
relations with China's National People's Congress (NPC), Speaker
Humayun Rasheed Chowdhury said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The group will comprise 11 lawmakers, covering all political
parties in the parliament, and will be responsible for looking
after the relations between the NPC and the Bangladeshi
parliament, Chowdhury said.
</P>
<P>
There exist good relations between the NPC and his country's
parliament, Chowdhury said in an exclusive interview with Xinhua,
ahead of an official goodwill visit to this South Asian nation by
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of China's NPC,
beginning Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chowdhury said he would discuss with Li ways to strengthen the
relations between the parliaments of the two countries, and the
proposed friendship group is a concrete measure to consolidate the
relations.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that there would be a similar group in China's NPC.
</P>
<P>
He said Li's coming visit is symbolic of a high-level
relationship between the two countries, and through the visit, the
relationship between the country's parliament and China's NPC will
become stronger.
</P>
<P>
"There are no problems in the relations between the two
countries," said Chowdhury, who has visited China many times.
</P>
<P>
He added that he was looking forward to visiting China again,
in his capacity as speaker, in the near future along with the
friendship group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
