<HEADLINE> Norwegians Protest Against NATO Air Strikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Members of 19 Norwegian
organizations staged a protest in front of the U.S. Embassy in
Norway Saturday afternoon to condemn NATO air strikes against
Yugoslavia, information reaching here said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
About 500 protesters chanted anti-U.S. and anti-NATO slogans
and waved banners, which said "stop bombing Yugoslavia" and "
Norway quits war."
</P>
<P>
The Norwegian capital of Oslo is the place where U.S. Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright is to meet Russian Foreign Minister
Igor Ivanov on Tuesday. 
</P>
