<HEADLINE> Dalian Coach Xu Announces Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Wanda coach Xu Genbao
announced he would resign following Sunday's 2-2 draw here with
Shenyang Haishi in China's professional soccer league.
</P>
<P>
Xu, a former national coach, said at the post-game press
conference he could not stand the huge pressure upon him.
</P>
<P>
"I want to resign because I can no longer brook it any more,"
Xu said after the defending champion had to rely on a goal two
minutes from time to grab a tie.
</P>
<P>
"The club may perform better if I resign now," said Xu, whose
team only managed four draws and one loss in five rounds this
season.
</P>
<P>
Club sources told Xinhua that Xu had told club management
before the match that he may resign if the result here turned
unsatisfactory. Now the club needed time to study Xu's decision.
</P>
<P>
Xu, 55, began to instruct the team in February, 1998 and guided
the club to league championship last year. 
