<HEADLINE> China's Regional Poverty Relief Cooperation Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao says that
cooperation in getting rid of poverty by more developed eastern
parts of the country and underdeveloped western parts is achieving
success.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark at a national conference on inter-regional
poverty relief that was held on April 9 in Guiyang, the capital of
Guizhou Province, where he urged the provinces and cities involved
to increase cooperation and to focus on improving the ecology and
solving food and clothing problems.
</P>
<P>
Wen is head of the State Council's Poverty-Eradication and
Development Leading Group. He said that in 1996 the State Council
drew up a program whereby 9 provinces and municipalities and four
cities with provincial economic decision-making power in the east
will assist 10 provinces and autonomous regions in the west.
</P>
<P>
Wen says that the program has far-reaching effects on economic
development and social progress in the poor areas and has provided
opportunities for economic development there. The two partners
need to carry out the program for mutual benefits in accordance
with market forces, he says.
</P>
<P>
China's goal to apply the national poverty-elimination plan,
whose pledge is to wipe out poverty in rural areas by 2000. The
developed areas have donated funds and material worth over one
billion yuan to the underdeveloped partners. They have reached
agreements on 2,600 projects involving 4 billion yuan in
investment.
</P>
<P>
Some 250,000 laborers from the western provinces and autonomous
regions have come to work in the eastern provinces and cities,
where they have earned more than 800 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
