<HEADLINE> Mysterious Disease in Afghanistan Diagnosed as Flu-A </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization
(WHO) has disclosed that the mysterious epidemic that killed over
200 people in Afghanistan was diagnosed as influenza-A, the
Associated Press of Pakistan reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The APP report said these people died due to lack of
antibiotic.
</P>
<P>
The disease, which was diagnosed after tests in Islamabad,
London and Geneva, was brought to the Darwaz locality of the
northeastern Badakhshan province in the middle of January by two
people who frequently visited the area, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The disease then spread rapidly with symptoms of fever,
headache, chest pain and cough. 
</P>
