<HEADLINE> Parliamentarians From 136 Countries Meet in Brussels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-Parliamentary Union (
IPU) inaugurated its 101st conference on Sunday as
parliamentarians from 136 countries all over the world gathered
here in Brussels to discuss issues of common concern on the eve of
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During their debates at the European Parliament, the European
Union (EU)'s main branch, the representatives will focus, in
particular, on parliamentary action to encourage all countries to
sign and ratify the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, to encourage
universal and non-discriminatory nuclear non-proliferation
measures and to work toward the eventual elimination of all
nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
They will also discuss the problem of metropolitan areas, a
global issue parliamentarians must respond in terms of urban
civilization and democracy, according to the agenda of the
conference.
</P>
<P>
The IPU sources said it is also possible to add to its agenda
an emergency supplementary item relating to the event of
particular international importance which occurred in the month
before or during the conference.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Federation Parliament has put forward a proposal in
this regard: "The situation in the Balkans and parliamentarians'
role in putting an end to the escalation of the NATO aggression
against Yugoslavia and in normalizing the situation in the region".
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the Belgian Federal Parliament, the week-
long IPU conference is hosting some 1,000 international delegates.
More than 600 parliamentarians, including 139 women, were
attending the meeting. 
</P>
