<HEADLINE> Urgent: Philippine Rebel Group Frees Another Hostage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The National Democratic Front
(NDF) freed a Philippine army officer Sunday in the Southern
Philippines, following its release of a police officer two days
ago, according to a local television report.
</P>
<P>
According to SNN television, Army Sgt. Alipio Lozada was freed
by the New People's Army, the armed wing of the NDF, in an
undisclosed place.
</P>
<P>
Lozada was captured by elements of the New People's Army after
an encounter near Tandag, Surigao del Sur, on March 5.
</P>
<P>
He is the second captive released by the New People's Army
within a week. The first was Chief Insp. Roberto Bernal who was
freed in Sorsogon Friday after 47 days of captivity.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, the NDF abducted five police and army
officers, including an army general, demanding exchange of
prisoners of war with the government. 
</P>
