<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Li Peng Arrives in Lahore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lahore, Pakistan, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, Chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
arrived here Sunday morning to continue his four-day official
visit to Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's acting Speaker of the National Assembly Jaffer
Iqbal, Chief Minister of the Punjab Province Shahbaz Sharif,
Punjab Governor Shahid Hamid and Mayor of Lahore Ahmad Hassan met
Li Peng at the Lahore International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng came to Islamabad, capital of Pakistan, last Thursday
after traveling to Greece, Turkey, and Syria on a six-nation trip
which will also bring the top legislator of China to Bangladesh
and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Islamabad, Li Peng had talks with Pakistan
National Assembly Speaker Bakhsh Soomro, Senate Chairman Wasim
Sajjad, Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, and President Rafique Tarar,
and exchanged views with them on bilateral relations and regional
and world issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
In Lahore, Li Peng is scheduled to meet leaders of the Punjab
Province and deliver a speech at a Civic Reception to be hosted by
the Punjab Chief Minister late Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Lahore, the second largest city of this South Asian nation and
also the provincial capital of Punjab, is one of the great Moghul
cities of the subcontinent which is rich in Muslim architecture.
It is also known as Pakistan's cultural and intellectual center.
</P>
