<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leading Trade Firm Strives to Expand Exports (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The China National Cereals, Oils
and Foodstuffs Import and Export Corporation (COFCO), one of the
country's largest foreign trade firms, has urged its employees to
try "a thousand and one ways" to expand exports in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Mingchen, chairman and president of the corporation, said
COFCO will explore every possible means to "maintain export growth
" this year in the face of "a much more severe export situation
than expected."
</P>
<P>
"I'm not optimistic in spite of last year's good results," said
Zhou in an interview with Xinhua. "The financial crisis has
reduced the purchase capacity of southeast Asian nations, and has
at the same time increased the competitiveness of their export
products. This year's difficulties related to exports will be much
more serious than we anticipated."
</P>
<P>
COFCO has been listed as one of the top 500 strongest companies
in the world for three consecutive years. The corporation's 1998
export volume surpassed 2.40 billion US dollars, up 19 percent on
1997 and a record volume since 1988. COFCO accounted for 1.3
percent of China's overall exports for last year.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said COFCO will attempt to increase exports by actively
engaging in processing, barter, counter and border trade, as well
as various other traditional trade forms.
</P>
<P>
He noted that COFCO will maintain and cultivate traditional
export market such as Europe, the United States, Japan and
Southeast Asia, and will simultaneously accelerate efforts to
explore potential markets such as Russia, Africa, the Middle East
and Latin America.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990411.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leading Trade Firm Strives to Expand Exports (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We will do our best to ensure the steady growth of 10-12 main
export products and will also develop new products and channels
for exports," said Zhou.
</P>
<P>
Since January this year, COFCO has dispatched representatives
to fruit, rice and meat production areas to scout for new export
products. Zhou said the corporation's goal is to reduce costs and
raise the quality of products.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to cultivate new growth points for exports yielded
positive results in the first quarter of the year, according to
Zhou. Exports of peanuts and peanut kernel have witnessed
noticeable growth in the wake of sluggish markets over the past
few years.
</P>
<P>
Zhou noted that exports of sesame and boiled bamboo shoots have
increased sharply.
</P>
<P>
He projected that the export volume for the first half of 1999
will be about the same or possibly slightly lower that the figure
for the same 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
"Our biggest worry at the moment is the small number of orders,
" said Zhou. "However, we are a leading state foreign trade
company and will continue our efforts throughout the year."
</P>
