<HEADLINE> Shi Guangsheng on Sino-Canadian Trade Relations (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
"China and Canada are influential countries across the Pacific
Ocean, sharing a tradition of friendship," Shi noted, adding that
there are no conflicts of fundamental interest.
</P>
<P>
"Economic and trade relations are a major part of the friendly
cooperative relations between the two nations," he added.
</P>
<P>
"Differences in social systems, history, culture and concept
of values should never obstruct the effective cooperation between
the two countries, and that has been proved over and over in past
years," Shi said.
</P>
<P>
"The two countries are economically complementary, and there
is great potential for bilateral economic and trade cooperation,"
he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
