<HEADLINE> Dutch Deputy PM Visits China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Prime Minister of the
Netherlands, Annemarie Jorritsma, arrived here today to kick off a
seven-day visit to China prior to a state visit by Queen Beatrix
Wilhelmina Armgard to the country.
</P>
<P>
Also minister of economic affairs, the deputy prime minister is
accompanied by a trade and economic delegation of people from more
than 40 Dutch big companies that involve sectors of finance,
transportation, contracting, manufacturing, energy, foodstuffs,
retailing and river dredging.
</P>
<P>
