Beijing, Jorritsma will also visit Shanghai and the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands is now China's third largest trade partner in
the European Union. China's exports to the Netherlands reached 5.
16 billion U.S. dollars last year, a 17.1 percent increase. In the
meantime, China's imports from the Netherlands dropped 22.3
percent to 833 million dollars, according to Chinese customs
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Dutch investments in China have grown by 70 percent annually
since 1994. The Netherlands ranks as China's 4th largest source of
foreign investments coming from EU nations, according to the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation. 
