<HEADLINE> Croatian Official on U.S. Lifting of Arms Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Croatia said Saturday that the U.S.
decision to lift arms embargo against it would enable it to
purchase arms and obtain military aid from the United States.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs Mate
Granic said over the Croatia television right after he returned
from a visit to the United States that he had discussed with U.S.
leaders issues on Croatia's joining the Partnership for Peace
program and the World Trade Organization.
</P>
