Kosovo crisis and Croatia's extensive reforms in its defense
system.
</P>
<P>
Croatian top leaders headed by President Franjo Tudjman were
determined to participate urgently in NATO's military actions
against Yugoslavia 15 days ago. In return, the United States said
that it will protect the security of Croatia if it is attacked on
revenge by Yugoslavia. 
