<HEADLINE> Croatia to Send Humanitarian Aid to Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Croatian government decided
Saturday to provide 2.6 million U.S. dollars worth of humanitarian
aid to Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
The donation from the country's commodities reserves will go to
Kosovo refugees in Albania and Macedonia, a statement issued by
the Croatian government said.
</P>
<P>
Aid to refugees in Albania includes 3,000 tons of flour, 60
tons of canned fish, 29 tons of canned meat and 12.5 tons of soap,
59 tons of detergent, some sanitary items and 3,000 blankets.
</P>
<P>
Commodities donated to refugees in Macedonia are 2,000 tons of
flour, 53 tons of canned fish, 11 tons of canned meat and 38 tons
of sanitary goods, the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
