<HEADLINE> Tunisia Books First Berth in African Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia clinched the first berth in
the African Cup of Nations finals after it beat Uganda 2-0 for its
fourth victory in as many qualifying games.
</P>
<P>
Hassan Gabsi opened the scoring in the 18th minute and Faouzi
Rouissi scored the second in the 41st, sending the country to its
fourth straight appearance in the finals of the biennial
continental championship.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia collected 12 points, eight points ahead of both Algeria
and Libera in group seven while Uganda fell to 0-1-3 and last in
the four-team group.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia joins defending champion Egypt and co-hosts Nigeria and
Ghana, which get automatic places in the finals.
</P>
<P>
Theodore Zue Nguema scored an 87th minute penalty kick in an 1-
0 upset Saturday over South Africa in Libreville, moving Gabon
into second place with six points in Group four. 
</P>
