<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Increase in Demand May Propel Bike Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- China's bicycle manufacturing
industry still has bright prospects in spite of the current
problems in the sector, according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Wang Fenghe, director of the china Bicycle Association, said
the bicycle industry could face the long term with confidence
given consumption trends on the domestic and international markets.
</P>
<P>
China has the largest population in the world but has very low
average per capita income, so its people are likely to continue
choosing bicycles as their preferred mode of transport for a long
time yet.
</P>
<P>
According to industry analysts, the rural market of one billion
people is the most promising for the future.
</P>
<P>
Fifty million bicycles are estimated to need replacement every
year in china. a renewal peak period expected in two or three
years may bring a new upsurge of bike buying.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of people's living conditions, a special
consumer group has appeared which uses bikes as exercise and
recreational tools. Their demand will further stimulate production.
</P>
<P>
Dure to the need to protect the environment and save energy,
the governments of some developed countries are taking measures to
encourage the use of bicycles.
</P>
<P>
Certain problems remain in the sector in China despite many
years of development, said Wang.
</P>
<P>
Owing to lack of rational macroeconomic measures, low level
reconstruction has created overcapacity and price cutting on the
domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Wang said the bicycle industry needed to produce more high-
quality bikes and improve after-sales service.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises must quicken their restructuring to control
output and act according to market economic principles if they
want to survive and forge ahead in the reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
