<HEADLINE> Tanjug: NATO Plane Shot Down in Northern Serbia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A NATO aircraft was shot down
over northern Serbia at 00:12 a.m. local time (22:12 GMT), Tanjug
news agency reported quoting eye witnesses.
</P>
<P>
The witnesses said they saw anti-aircraft fire hit a plane
over a village between Sombor and Odzak in Voivodina province,
about 200 kilometers northwest of Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
