<HEADLINE> Germany Eliminated to Send Nigeria Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria entered the second round of
the World Youth soccer championships on Saturday after Germany
suffered a shock defeat by Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
Germany was eliminated after they were upset by Costa Rica 2-1,
giving a lift to the hosts who had bowed to Paraguay 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay upset Nigeria in the first 20 minutes with the goals
from Sergio Fernandez and Ruben Maldonado with the hosts pulling
one back before the break by Ganiyu Shittu.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay finished top of group A with Nigeria second from Costa
Rica on goal difference and Germany placed last. The top two teams
in each of the six groups go through plus the best four third-
placed teams.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica, who will have to wait for the outcome of Sunday's
games to know if they can go through, pulled off the surprising
victory through Alberto Brenes and Esteban Santana. In between,
Christian Timm scored for Germany, who had Andreas Voss sent off
for a rash tackle.
</P>
<P>
Ghana ended up atop group B after hammering Kazakhstan 3-0 in
Kaduna, with two goals by Baffour Gyan and one by Totu Adu, all in
the second half.
</P>
<P>
Croatia and Argentina fought to a dull 0-0 tie which sent both
teams through, the latter ensuring themselves a place as one of
the best third-placed teams.
</P>
<P>
Mexico, who are already qualified for the next round, topped
the group C after they drew 1-1 with Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Luis Gonzalez scored for Mexico but Saleh Al Saqri levelled the
scoring for the homeward-bound Saudis.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Ireland also moved ahead as they routed Australia 4-0
to claim second spot with Damien Duff involved in the first two
goals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
