<HEADLINE> Over 340,000 Tourists Visit Myanmar in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A total of 340,123 foreign
tourists visited Myanmar in 1998, of whom 182,399 came over by
land routes through border points.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures published by the country's
Central Statistical Organization, the number of tourists who
visited Myanmar in the year increased by only 10,963 as compared
with that in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Despite some rise in the number of tourists, Myanmar's tourism
business is still depressed, partly due to the Asian financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, there were 523 hotels with 14,714 rooms in
Myanmar, while there were only 39 hotels with 1,240 rooms ten
years ago in 1988, according to the statistics available here.
