<HEADLINE> Sex Education Via TV in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is to break new ground
again in China, this time by broadcasting a series of sex
education programs on its local TV station, the first time this
has happened anywhere in the country.
</P>
<P>
The program is a result of cooperation between the Shanghai
Municipal Family Planning Commission and the local television
station and the first of the 52, twenty minute long, episodes
starts next month.
</P>
<P>
Topics will deal with adult and juvenile sexual behavior and
sexual health, particularly offering advice on dealing with
venereal and other related diseases.
</P>
<P>
Local people in Shanghai have been asking for information on
family planning, health care for mothers and children and safe
sexual practices which has largely not been available.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey highlighted that 54 percent of the city's
citizens thought the mass media was the best vehicle and this
spurred on the Shanghai authorities to set up the joint project
with the tv station. 
</P>
