<HEADLINE> Three Dead, Seven Missing As Bridge Collapses in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Three people drowned in a river
and seven were missing after a week-long heavy rain in western
Venezuela, official sources said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Lara State Civil Defense Director Hector Azaul told the press
that up to the moment only three bodies of seven missing persons
have been found. They were swept Friday by the "Turbio" river
after an 80 meter bridge collapsed.
</P>
<P>
When the bridge collapsed, one of the children who were
observing the rise of the river water was able to grasp the
branches of a plant, which enabled him to reach an islet where he
was rescued by a National Guard helicopter.
</P>
<P>
Azaul said the rising water caused the collapse of three other
bridges, which left some 800,000 persons incommunicado until next
Monday, when military bridges will be completed.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rains have also affected areas in the east and the
west of the country, as well as the central littoral near Caracas.
</P>
</TEXT>
