<HEADLINE> Electronics Industry Promising in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The electronics industry has good
prospects and potential in Tianjin Municipality and promises to be
a sound investment field for foreign businesses, the city's vice
mayor said in a meeting with a United States business delegation.
</P>
<P>
"The Tianjin Development Zone (TDZ) is the key area for
developing the electronics industry in the city and a future base
for China's information industry," said Ye Disheng, vice mayor of
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin imported more than 700 million U.S.dollars worth of
semiconductor products, and most semiconductor materials needed in
the city still depend on imports, according to the vice mayor.
</P>
<P>
The city has already attracted to its development zone an
electronics business group producing mobile telecommunications
equipment, PCs and compatible products, machinery, semiconductor
products, and automated meters.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 500 joint-venture electronics companies have been set up
in the zone, involving a total investment of about three billion U.
S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Investments in electronics in the TDN accounts for one-third of
the total investment attracted to the development zone, and
electronics enterprises contribute almost half of the output value,
exports, and taxes in the district. 
</P>
