<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Private Sector Active in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's private sector has
emerged as the biggest importer and exporter due to the positive
policy adopted by the government in foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official data compiled by the Central
Statistical Organization, the country's total import in 1998
amounted to 2.824 billion U.S. dollars, of which the private
sector shared 1.864 billion dollars or 66 percent, while the state
sector represented 960 million dollars or 34 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of the country's total export volume of 1.137 billion dollars
in 1998, the private sector took up 819.5 million dollars or 72
percent, while the state sector represented 318 million dollars or
28 percent.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Myanmar adopted a positive policy towards the
private sector such as leasing out some bad-running state-owned
small, medium and large economic enterprises to private
entrepreneurs who have technical skill, sound management and
strong financial backing, and implementing some related
preferential policies for them in foreign trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
