<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Archeologists Unearth Ancient Tombs in Kunming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists recently
unearthed an ancient tomb complex dating to the Han Dynasty (206-
24 B.C.) in the eastern suburbs of Kunming, capital of Yunnan
Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 tombs have been unearthed in an area covering
over 16,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
A member of the archeological team said that hundreds of tombs
have been or will be excavated. He added that experts have already
discovered over 2,000 cultural relics from the tombs, including
lacquered woodcarvings and bronze cooking vessels, kettles and
weapons.
</P>
<P>
The discovery, which represents the largest group of ancient
tombs thus far discovered in the province, will provide valuable
clues for research into the city's history and ancient society.
</P>
</TEXT>
