ZHENGZHOU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The environment protection
bureau in Zhengzhou, capital of Henan Province, recently issued a
regulation ordering the resumption of controls on motor vehicle
emissions.
</P>
<P>
Initial examinations were carried out over a three month
period from May to August last year.
</P>
<P>
The city decided to initiate a new round of strict
examinations in order to further improve the city's air quality.
</P>
<P>
Zhengzhou suffers from severe air pollution, some 85 percent
of which is due to motor vehicle emissions. Half of the city's 300,
000 motor vehicles fail to meet exhaust emission standards.
</P>
<P>
All motor vehicles being sold or operating in the city will be
subject to emission control examinations, according to the
regulation. All vehicles sold or in operation will be required to
meet related standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
