<HEADLINE> China Accelerates Railway Construction in Southwest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- China has initiated a new round
of construction on the railway line liking Neijiang, in southwest
China's Sichuan Province, with Kunming, capital of Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The project commenced in June last year and first phase has
been completed after nine months at a cost of 3.05 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The line, one of the country's key railway projects, will be
completed over the next four years at an estimated cost of 11.6
billion yuan (1.4 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The 854-km Neijing-Kunming Railway will pass through several
cities in Sichuan, Guizhou and Yunnan provinces.
</P>
<P>
The line, which will be an important part of China's north-
south railway network, will alleviate transportation bottlenecks
in the southwest China and accelerate tourism and natural
resources development in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
