<HEADLINE> Yugoslav President Asks his People to Help in National Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic Saturday called on his countrymen to do their part in
restoring major facilities damaged by NATO air attacks.
</P>
<P>
If all Yugoslav citizens do their own jobs well and even better
in wartime than in peaceful period, that would be a best answer to
the aggressors, the president said while meeting Yugoslav and Serb
leaders on the reconstruction of facilities vital to the country
but damaged by NATO's bombs.
</P>
<P>
During wartime, the president said, the Yugoslav people should
overcome tremendous difficulties and do more and better, thus
proving to the world that the Yugoslav nation is a heroic nation.
</P>
<P>
Since March 24, NATO has sent more than 3,000 airplanes to bomb
Yugoslavia. Some 450 cruise missiles were fired from 20 naval
vessels, including two aircraft carriers. Thousands of tons of
bombs were dumped on Yugoslav territory.
</P>
<P>
Apart from military facilities, civil facilities such as
resident buildings factories, mines, airports, roads, bridges,
communication systems, hospitals and schools were also bombed by
NATO, causing an estimated loss of 100 billion U.S. dollars to the
Yugoslav Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
