<HEADLINE> Villeneuve Faces Punishment over Illegal Fuel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Former world champion Jacques
Villeneuve looks certain to lose his 16th position on the grid for
the Brazilian Formula One Grand Prix after tournament officials
found his car was running on illegal fuel, According to reports
from Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
A statement from stewards at the Interlagos circuit confirmed
that a fuel sample was "not the same as the one which had been
approved for use by the relevant competitor prior to the event".
</P>
<P>
Villeneuve could be disqualified from the event or be forced to
start from the back of the grid. A decision will be made at a
stewards meeting on Saturday evening.
</P>
