<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills 15 in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- 15 people have died and
152 are missing after landslides occurred in several Colombian
zones, government authorities said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Landslides caused by rains have brought damage to some 4,000
people residing near the banks of several rivers, where the state
of alert was declared.
</P>
<P>
Disaster Attention and Prevention Office Director Monica
Yamhure said that the worst-hit area is in the Inza municipality
zone, in the El Cauca department.
</P>
<P>
A landslide buried 15 inhabitants and several homes, while at
least 12 people were reported missing in the zone.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of hectares of cultivations have been affected in the
flooded areas. Roads and dozens of houses are under water. 
</P>
